[2] Cholera - Uganda (Amuru District)
Date: Fri 28 Oct 2016
Source: The Monitor [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201610280002.html


At least 2 people have died of cholera in Amuru District, with cases registered rising to 40 patients since the outbreak of the epidemic in September 2016, according to statistics from the district health officials. The in-charge of Bibia Health Centre III in Atiak Sub-county, Ms Susan Aromorach, said the latest case registered was on 22 Oct 2016, when 4 people were admitted to the facility.

Ms Aromorach said that among the 4 patients who had been admitted, 2 were children, and they have since been discharged, while one person is still admitted in the isolation ward.

