[3] Cholera - Niger (Dosso Region)
Date: Thu 27 Oct 2016
Source: Life and Style [machine trans. edited]
https://vidayestilo.terra.com.co/salud/nueve-muertos-y-14-hospitalizados-por-colera-en-el-sur-de-niger,4e2076782b6548149e7e5d1f9d56dfeepgbpixfx.html


At least 9 people died in the last 2 weeks, and another 14 were treated in hospitals because of the cholera epidemic in a rural area in the Dosso region in southern Niger, the Nigerian Minister of Health, Idi Mainasara, reported today, 27 Oct 2016.

"In total, 23 people were affected in the region (rural Bella); 6 of them died. The remaining 17 patients were admitted to hospitals, and 3 of them later died," said Mainasara to government radio.

The 1st case was identified on 13 Oct 2016, when a 16-year-old was admitted to hospital after suffering disease symptoms, such as abdominal pain, diarrhea and vomiting. The young man died the day after admission. "On 16 Oct 2016, 4 other villagers in the area died after suffering the same clinical signs of the disease," said Mainasara.

