[5] Cholera - Philippines (Negros Occidental Province)
Date: Thu 27 Oct 2016
Source: The Visayan Daily Star [edited]
http://www.visayandailystar.com/2016/October/27/topstory4.htm


The Bacolod City Health Office has declared a cholera outbreak in Handumanan Elementary School 1 in Bacolod City after 10 out of the more than 100 students affected by food and waterborne disease tested positive for cholera.

Dr. Grace Tan, CHO Environmental Sanitation Division head, said they are taking steps to prevent the disease from spreading. As of yesterday [26 Oct 2016], however, no additional cases of cholera were noted in HES 1. Out of the 10 affected by cholera, one was an adult, she said.

Tan said that all the 129 students affected by the food and waterborne disease in HES 1 have already been discharged from the different hospitals where they had been confined between 14 and 17 Oct 2016.

They are consolidating the records since there were children affected by food and waterborne disease who had not been accounted for, since they were only treated at home and did not pass through the health centers. They could all be accounted for when they return to school in November 2016, she said.

[Byline: Chrysee Samillano]

